Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.71,0:01:23.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,托马斯勋爵\N{\rEng}Lord Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.78,0:01:27.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,亨利勋爵\N{\rEng}Lord Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.42,0:01:30.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,安布罗斯勋爵\N{\rEng}Lord Ambrose.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.55,0:01:33.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,罗伯特勋爵\N{\rEng}Lord Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.42,0:01:37.82,Chs,,0,0,0,,沃尔特勋爵\N{\rEng}Lord Walter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.26,0:01:44.55,Chs,,0,0,0,,你最好别让我失望 查尔斯·格雷 我在你身上押了二十畿尼\N{\rEng}You'd better not let me down, Charles Grey. I've got 20 guineas riding on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.90,0:01:47.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,只有二十？如果换成我押 我就押四十\N{\rEng}Only 20? I'd double that if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.74,0:01:53.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,走 女士们\N{\rEng}Come on, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.20,0:01:57.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,10)\fs38\blur2\pos(970,645)\c&HB1E6DA&}英格兰 阿尔索普庄园  一七七四年四月
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.55,0:02:02.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,先生们 绕着跑两圈 听我口令\N{\rEng}Gentlemen, twice around the course, on my count.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.05,0:02:06.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,三 二…\N{\rEng}Three, two,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.02,0:02:10.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,一！\N{\rEng}one!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.39,0:02:11.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 跑啊 格雷先生！ - 跑啊 托马斯！\N{\rEng}- Come on, Mr. Grey!  - Come on, Thomas!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.03,0:02:15.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 跑啊 格雷先生！ - 跑啊 沃尔特勋爵！\N{\rEng}- Come on, Mr. Grey!  - Run, Lord Walter!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.53,0:02:17.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,跑啊 格雷先生！\N{\rEng}Come on, Mr. Grey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.47,0:02:20.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,跑啊 格雷先生 别慢吞吞的\N{\rEng}Come on, Mr. Grey. You're tired already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.24,0:02:22.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 跑啊 格雷先生！ - 再快点！\N{\rEng}- Come on, Mr. Grey!  - Faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.95,0:02:40.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,大人觉得乔治安娜还漂亮么？\N{\rEng}I trust Your Grace still finds Georgiana an attractive girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:42.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,当然了 斯宾塞夫人\N{\rEng}Of course, Lady Spencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.62,0:02:46.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,她是上流社会的才女 知节守礼\N{\rEng}She's an accomplished lady of quality and devoted to her duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:49.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,能说流利的法语 意大利语和拉丁语\N{\rEng}She's fluent in French, Italian, Latin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.30,0:02:52.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,精通骑术和舞仪 还…\N{\rEng}and fully versed in horsemanship and dancing and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.20,0:02:56.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,是的 这些我都知道 她是您的骄傲\N{\rEng}Yes, I'm aware of all that. She's a credit to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:02:59.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,我实在想不出有什么\N{\rEng}I can't think of anything that would stand in the way
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.84,0:03:02.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,能阻碍一场天作之合\N{\rEng}of a singularly happy marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.11,0:03:05.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵大人并不顾虑这些 斯宾塞夫人\N{\rEng}These are not the issues that burden the Duke, Lady Spencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:08.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,大人有繁衍子嗣之责\N{\rEng}It is His Grace's duty to produce an heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.82,0:03:10.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,反言之 若能为大人生下承业之子\N{\rEng}On the other hand, your daughter may expect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.29,0:03:12.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,你的女儿必有厚报\N{\rEng}a handsome reward when that occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.85,0:03:16.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 希顿  - 大人\N{\rEng}- Thank you, Heaton.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.33,0:03:19.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,大人您尽可放心\N{\rEng}Your Grace may rest assured.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:22.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,本家族女子在这方面从未有失\N{\rEng}The women in our family have never forfeited on that account.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:26.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,那好 既然有此保证…\N{\rEng}Well, with that assurance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:37.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,就这么办吧\N{\rEng}So be it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.71,0:03:41.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,冲啊 格雷先生！\N{\rEng}Come on, Mr. Grey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:53.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,很抱歉 女士们 我的马赢了\N{\rEng}I do apologize, ladies, but it appears that my horse has won.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:57.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,查尔斯 再比一次试试\N{\rEng}Beat me again, Charles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:02.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 干得好 格雷先生  - 干得好\N{\rEng}- Well done, Mr. Grey.  - Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.07,0:04:05.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我们欠你多少？ - 你欠我四十\N{\rEng}- So how much do we owe you?  - You owe me 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.71,0:04:09.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 二十 四十  - 我的奖赏呢？\N{\rEng}- Twenty, 40.  - My reward?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.95,0:04:17.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,你想要什么？\N{\rEng}And what do you suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:20.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,你母亲要见你 乔治安娜小姐\N{\rEng}Your mother wishes to see you, Lady Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:33.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.39,0:04:52.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,对不起 妈妈 是不是我们太吵了？\N{\rEng}I must apologize, Mama. Were we making too much noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.95,0:04:54.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,不 我亲爱的\N{\rEng}Not at all, my darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.62,0:04:57.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,有重要事跟你说 过来\N{\rEng}We have more important things to talk of. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:09.50,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我听到一个传言  - 什么传言？\N{\rEng}- I have heard a rumor.  - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.91,0:05:12.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,我很快就要给我的女儿梳妆打扮\N{\rEng}That I will soon be addressing my daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:15.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,她很快就要变成德文郡公爵夫人了\N{\rEng}as Her Grace, the Duchess of Devonshire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:20.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 是真的吗 妈妈？ - 是的\N{\rEng}- Is it true, Mama?  - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:24.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,德文郡公爵？\N{\rEng}The Duke of Devonshire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:32.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,我本想将你晚些嫁人 至少等到十八岁\N{\rEng}I had hoped not to part with you until 18 at the soonest,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.29,0:05:33.32,Chs,,0,0,0,,但有天赐良缘在前\N{\rEng}but, with such a fine match,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:36.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,再不放你走 我就太自私了\N{\rEng}it would be selfish of me not to let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.13,0:05:38.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 他爱我么？ - 当然爱啦\N{\rEng}- He loves me?  - Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.13,0:05:39.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我只见过他两次\N{\rEng}I have only met him twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:41.43,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果是真心相爱\N{\rEng}When one truly loves someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:43.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,不需要知根知底也能明白答案\N{\rEng}one doesn't have to know them well to be sure, Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.07,0:05:46.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,这就是一见倾心\N{\rEng}One feels it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.54,0:05:53.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我确信 你跟他会幸福的  - 肯定会的 妈妈 我知道\N{\rEng}- I do believe you will be happy with him.  - I shall, Mama. I know I shall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.40,0:07:28.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,10)\fs80\fsp8\shad3\blur2\pos(1000,630)\c&HD5E6E4&\4a&H00&}公爵夫人
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:32.87,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 来啊！ - 她来了！\N{\rEng}- Come on!  - She's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.98,0:07:35.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵夫人！公爵夫人！\N{\rEng}Your Grace! Your Grace!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.16,0:07:44.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 是她！ - 公爵夫人！\N{\rEng}- There she is!  - Duchess!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.99,0:07:47.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,他们想要干嘛？\N{\rEng}What do they want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:50.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,当然是想来看我 还有我的新婚妻子\N{\rEng}To see me and my new wife, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.50,0:07:55.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,也许会觉得讨厌 但你会很快习惯的\N{\rEng}It can be a nuisance, but you'll get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:36.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,10)\fs38\shad2\blur1\pos(970,770)\c&HD5E6E4&}伦敦 德文郡公爵宅邸
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.69,0:08:53.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,欢迎您 夫人\N{\rEng}Welcome, Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.04,0:09:12.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,来啊 小伙子们 雨果 雨果 过来\N{\rEng}Come, boys. Come on. Hugo, Hugo. Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.08,0:09:16.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,好 好 好 好\N{\rEng}Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.75,0:09:21.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,很好 对了 往这儿来\N{\rEng}It's all right. Yes, yes. This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.89,0:09:24.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,雨果 来 过来\N{\rEng}Hugo. Come, boy. Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:05.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,剪刀给我 你们退下\N{\rEng}Scissors. You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:40.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,我这一辈子 一直没弄明白\N{\rEng}For the life of me, I could never understand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:44.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,为什么女人的衣服设计得如此繁复\N{\rEng}why women's clothes must be so damn complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:49.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,这是我们女人用来表达自己的方式\N{\rEng}It's just our way of expressing ourselves, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.11,0:10:55.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,你这话什么意思？\N{\rEng}Whatever do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.98,0:10:59.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,你们男人可以有很多途径表达自己\N{\rEng}Well, you have so many ways of expressing yourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.65,0:11:03.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,而我们只能通过帽子和衣饰来表达\N{\rEng}whereas we must make do with our hats and our dresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.33,0:11:40.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,请你上床去 好么？\N{\rEng}Would you go to the bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.96,0:12:47.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,一个人必须履行自己的责任\N{\rEng}One has to accept one's responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.76,0:12:49.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,也许有些事看起来难以承受\N{\rEng}Certain obligations come with marriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:51.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,但结了婚就得在某些方面尽义务\N{\rEng}no matter how burdensome they may seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.57,0:12:54.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,我懂 但当我和他在一起的时候…\N{\rEng}Yes, but when we are together...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:59.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,我是说我们在一起亲密的时候\N{\rEng}But when we are together, intimately, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.94,0:13:02.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,我知道 是有点烦人\N{\rEng}I know. It can be a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.38,0:13:05.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,等你给他养了儿子就好了\N{\rEng}However, it is only until you have given him a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.25,0:13:09.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,这种事会越来越少 他也不会逼你做了\N{\rEng}Then the occasions will become fewer and less determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:11.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果他时不时跟我说些什么\N{\rEng}I think it might feel different
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.65,0:13:14.52,Chs,,0,0,0,,也许我会感觉好一点\N{\rEng}if he would talk to me every once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.62,0:13:18.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,不是说他不够亲切 但他从不和我说话\N{\rEng}I mean, it's not that he's unkind, but he never talks to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:19.96,Chs,,0,0,0,,我本以为他会像爸爸一样\N{\rEng}I thought that he would be like Papa,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.06,0:13:22.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,在那冰冷的外表下\N{\rEng}that under his cool reserve
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.30,0:13:24.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,深藏着一颗多愁善感的心\N{\rEng}there'd be a wealth of depth and sentiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.00,0:13:30.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,但他对什么都不感兴趣 除了他的狗\N{\rEng}but he isn't interested in anything, apart from his dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:32.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,对公爵大人别太苛求了 乔\N{\rEng}Try not to be too hard on His Grace, G.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:35.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,他只想好好履行他的职责\N{\rEng}He's merely intent on fulfilling his duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.74,0:13:40.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,你说想跟他交流 但又有什么好说的呢？\N{\rEng}And as for talking to him, well, whatever is there to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.21,0:13:42.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,您说得也没错\N{\rEng}No, you're quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:45.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,我太傻了 还以为凭自己的水平\N{\rEng}How foolish of me to think that I should be able to converse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.29,0:13:47.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,能和我的丈夫交流\N{\rEng}with my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.39,0:13:51.38,Chs,,0,0,0,,耐心 坚忍和顺从 这些是你的武器\N{\rEng}Georgiana, equip yourself with patience, fortitude and resignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.49,0:13:54.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,你很快就会有儿子 到那时你就明白了\N{\rEng}A boy will come soon enough, and then you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.50,0:14:09.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,而我们辉格党(该党反对绝对王权) 认为只有这样才是明智的选择\N{\rEng}But we, the Whig Party, simply see this as just, right and sensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.24,0:14:15.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,让独立之号角响彻美利坚 用黎明的丧钟送走奴隶制\N{\rEng}Just to bring independence to America. Right to abolish the slave trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.68,0:14:20.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,引自由之风吹拂普罗大众\N{\rEng}And sensible to bring freedom to the common man,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.52,0:14:25.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,在英格兰这片神宠之地\N{\rEng}so the blessings of this blessed plot, this England,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.59,0:14:30.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,所有子民能同享上帝的恩泽光辉\N{\rEng}may be more equally enjoyed by all of its inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:40.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,请各位为宴会主人 也是我党的赞助人\N{\rEng}I would like to propose a toast to our host and benefactor
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.88,0:14:45.87,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵大人和美丽的新晋公爵夫人举杯\N{\rEng}His Grace the Duke and his beautiful new Duchess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:47.78,Chs,,0,0,0,,请各位起身\N{\rEng}Please be upstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:57.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 公爵大人和夫人！ - 公爵大人和夫人！\N{\rEng}- The Duke and Duchess!  - The Duke and Duchess!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.70,0:15:09.43,Chs,,0,0,0,,很精彩的演说 福克斯先生\N{\rEng}Excellent speech, Mr. Fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.54,0:15:12.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢夸奖 在一群人之前演说总是不难\N{\rEng}I thank you. It is always easier to address a congregation of friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.84,0:15:16.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,尤其是当这帮人已经喝醉的时候\N{\rEng}particularly when those friends are drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.84,0:15:20.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人对福克斯先生的演讲有何高见？\N{\rEng}And how did the Duchess find Mr. Fox's speech?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.85,0:15:24.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,我得承认 我还不习惯政治演说\N{\rEng}I must confess, I am not yet at ease with political speeches.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.29,0:15:27.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,特别的遣词方式总让我 摸不透背后的真正含义\N{\rEng}Their very form tends to obstruct my view of their actual meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.52,0:15:29.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,…如果那些言语另有所指\N{\rEng}if such there be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.72,0:15:31.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,不知演说中哪部分的言语\N{\rEng}In which particular section of the speech
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.76,0:15:34.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,让夫人感到“困惑”呢？\N{\rEng}did the message elude Your Grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:39.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,总的来说 我非常赞同您的观点\N{\rEng}Well, I have great sympathy with your sentiments in general,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.47,0:15:44.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我不明白您说的“我们辉格党人”\N{\rEng}but I fail to fully comprehend how far we, the Whig Party, that is,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.37,0:15:47.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,对自由一词的推行力度到底有多深\N{\rEng}are fully committed to the concept of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.27,0:15:50.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我们主张扩大选举权范围  - 让所有人参加选举？\N{\rEng}- We intend to extend the vote.  - To all men?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.31,0:15:54.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,当然不是 但肯定不止现在这些人 所谓“适度的自由”\N{\rEng}Heavens, no. But certainly to more men. Freedom in moderation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.88,0:15:57.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,-“适度的自由”？ - 完全正确\N{\rEng}- "Freedom in moderation"?  - Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.95,0:16:01.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,我相信您的苦心孤诣 福克斯先生\N{\rEng}I'm sure you are full of the best intentions, Mr. Fox,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:03.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我要说 如果我有选举权\N{\rEng}but I dare say I would not spend my vote,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.09,0:16:08.79,Chs,,0,0,0,,如此模糊的声明是无法赢得我的选票的\N{\rEng}if I had it, of course, on so vague a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:13.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,一个人要么自由 要么没有自由 自由的定义只有一种\N{\rEng}One is either free or one is not. The concept of freedom is an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.30,0:16:15.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,不可能有人适度的死亡\N{\rEng}After all, one cannot be moderately dead
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:19.87,Chs,,0,0,0,,也不可能有适度的相爱 或者适度的自由\N{\rEng}or moderately loved or moderately free.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.97,0:16:22.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,这永远是一个非正即反的问题\N{\rEng}It must always remain a matter of either or.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.38,0:16:29.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,我想来说几句\N{\rEng}I think it appropriate to say a few words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.65,0:16:30.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,当…\N{\rEng}When...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:56.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,你去卧室里找找\N{\rEng}Could you check the chamber
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.28,0:16:57.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 看能不能找到…  - 大人\N{\rEng}- and see if you can find...  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.58,0:17:00.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,…其他样式的法国蕾丝？\N{\rEng}...different kinds of French lace?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.48,0:17:05.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 有什么问题嘛？ - 没有\N{\rEng}- Is anything the matter?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.76,0:17:11.16,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 您离席了  - 嗯 我已经吃完了\N{\rEng}- You just left.  - Yes. Well, I had done eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.26,0:17:13.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,那些无聊的讲话我听厌了 烦死了\N{\rEng}and those damn speeches bore me to distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:16.16,Chs,,0,0,0,,看来下次得下禁令 不得发言\N{\rEng}I think we have to ban them in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.26,0:17:20.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,但您是辉格党的主要拥护人啊\N{\rEng}But you are the Whigs' main supporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.33,0:17:22.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,没错 我对政治并不反感\N{\rEng}Yes. Well, I've no problem with the politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.00,0:17:25.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,只是我无法忍受那些个夸夸其谈\N{\rEng}It's just the rhetoric I can't stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.61,0:17:33.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 要我陪您去么？ - 我看不用了 这又何必呢？\N{\rEng}- Shall I come with you?  - No. I mean, why ever should you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.97,0:18:00.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵一切都好 只想小憩片刻\N{\rEng}The Duke is perfectly well. He simply wanted to rest a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.81,0:18:02.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,先生们 请坐吧\N{\rEng}Do sit down, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:13.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,是不是公爵对演讲的长度颇有微辞啊？\N{\rEng}Was it the length of the speech that got the better of the Duke?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:16.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,当然不是\N{\rEng}Certainly not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:17.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,他非常喜欢您的演讲\N{\rEng}He enjoyed it immensely
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.83,0:18:21.56,Chs,,0,0,0,,他还说希望下次的演讲再长一些就好了\N{\rEng}and expressed a hope that next time it would be even longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.40,0:18:26.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人请  - 福克斯先生请\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Mr. Fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.09,0:18:57.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 发生了什么事？ - 跟你无关\N{\rEng}- What's going on?  - Nothing to concern you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:02.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我不明白  - 到这边来\N{\rEng}- I don't understand.  - Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.51,0:19:15.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,今晚你看上去很漂亮 裙子是你自己设计的？\N{\rEng}You look very beautiful tonight. Is this dress your design?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:20.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,是的 谢谢\N{\rEng}Yes, it is. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.76,0:19:31.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,我想你应该不会反对你的丈夫…\N{\rEng}Then I think you should allow your husband to appreciate it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.17,0:19:33.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,对这裙子做进一步的欣赏吧\N{\rEng}in a little more detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:36.67,Chs,,0,0,0,,过来\N{\rEng}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.53,0:20:11.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 好 让他们进来  - 有客人？\N{\rEng}- Yes, send them in.  - Are we having company?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.77,0:20:15.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,你不觉得这羊肉味道有些奇怪么？\N{\rEng}Don't you think this mutton has a funny taste?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.48,0:20:21.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 没有 我觉得很好  - 我觉得有点奇怪\N{\rEng}- No. Not really, no.  - I think it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.16,0:20:36.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔 这是夏洛特 以后她和我们一起住\N{\rEng}G, this is Charlotte, and she will be staying with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.57,0:20:41.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,为什么？\N{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.31,0:20:57.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,因为她妈妈死了 她也没有别的地方可去\N{\rEng}Because her mother is dead, and she has no other place to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:03.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,你是这孩子的父亲？\N{\rEng}Have you fathered that child?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.16,0:21:10.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,她只是…只是一个小姑娘 乔 又不是什么世界末日\N{\rEng}It's... It's only a little girl, G. It's hardly the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.07,0:21:16.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你想让我照顾她？ - 这儿有很多空房间\N{\rEng}- Are you expecting me to look after her?  - We have a house full of vacant rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.74,0:21:19.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,她不会打扰你的 事实上 她还能帮到你\N{\rEng}She needn't bother you. In fact, she may even be of use to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.51,0:21:22.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,可以先学着如何做母亲\N{\rEng}You can practice your mothering skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.94,0:21:27.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,直到我们的儿子出世\N{\rEng}until our son arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.62,0:21:32.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,嗯 这羊肉味道肯定不对\N{\rEng}No, this doesn't taste like normal mutton.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.25,0:21:36.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,肯定是有东西串了味 把它拿走好么？\N{\rEng}I'm sure there is something the matter with it. Could you take it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.99,0:21:42.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,你觉得这羊肉味道对不对？\N{\rEng}Does it taste like normal mutton?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.66,0:21:47.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,是不是有股味儿啊？给我过来\N{\rEng}Does it taste like normal mutton? Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.00,0:21:52.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,觉得这羊肉味道对不对啊 小刁嘴？\N{\rEng}Think it tastes like normal mutton, fussy dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.21,0:21:54.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,谁是小刁嘴啊？\N{\rEng}Who's a fussy mutton dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.12,0:22:09.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,你的娃娃有名字么？\N{\rEng}Does your doll have a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.06,0:22:17.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,我打赌 她一定喜欢自己的新卧室\N{\rEng}I bet you she loves being in her new bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.13,0:22:24.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,给她取个名字吧 明天告诉我\N{\rEng}You'll have to think of a name and let me know tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.17,0:22:27.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,你能给她想个好名字 对不对夏洛特？\N{\rEng}Do you think you'll be able to do that, Charlotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.31,0:22:30.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,我…\N{\rEng}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.74,0:22:33.68,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 请你先出去好么？ - 夫人…\N{\rEng}- Would you leave us, please?  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.33,0:22:47.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,你好 夏洛特\N{\rEng}Hello, Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.07,0:22:55.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,我叫乔治安娜\N{\rEng}My name is Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.56,0:23:22.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 晚上好  - 谢谢\N{\rEng}- Good evening.  - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.53,0:23:27.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,晚上好 女士们\N{\rEng}Good evening, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.94,0:23:34.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人 您的肚子要是再长一寸 估计就会爆开\N{\rEng}An inch more and I do believe Your Grace will explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.11,0:23:37.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,恭维方面 谢里顿总是很在行\N{\rEng}Sheridan always knows how to pay a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.44,0:23:39.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,还得再等几周\N{\rEng}Still a few more weeks to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.11,0:23:42.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,这么大的肚子 在您身上那是再合适不过了\N{\rEng}A huge belly has never been more becoming on anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.22,0:23:46.24,Chs,,0,0,0,,这方面福克斯是专家 他每次经过镜子\N{\rEng}Well, Fox, here, offers an expert opinion seeing, as he does, a giant belly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:48.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,都能看到一个超大号的肚子\N{\rEng}every time he passes a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.59,0:23:51.25,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果把您的肚子搁到一个女人的身上 大家都会明白那是怎么回事\N{\rEng}If your belly were on a woman, well, we'd all know what to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.36,0:23:55.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,我亲爱的谢里顿 一小时之前 我的肚子就搁在一个女人的身上\N{\rEng}My dear Sheridan, an hour ago my belly was on a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.16,0:23:56.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,你明白是怎么回事了么？\N{\rEng}Now what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.03,0:24:01.16,Chs,,0,0,0,,以后再想冒犯福克斯先生 在开口之前最好先想清楚\N{\rEng}That will teach you to insult Mr. Fox before the gaming has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.54,0:24:07.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,画得不错\N{\rEng}It's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.15,0:24:15.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,下注时间结束\N{\rEng}No more bets, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:23.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,七点\N{\rEng}Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.69,0:24:27.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人又赢了\N{\rEng}Her Grace wins again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.96,0:24:31.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,再赌一轮吗？\N{\rEng}Another wager?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.27,0:24:36.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 您没事吧 夫人？ - 夫人！\N{\rEng}- Are you all right, Your Grace?  - Your Grace!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.28,0:24:45.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,是产前阵痛么？我妻子要生产了\N{\rEng}Are those labor pains? My wife is in labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.01,0:24:46.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,跟我走\N{\rEng}Come along.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.08,0:24:49.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,我想现在值得举杯庆祝\N{\rEng}I think this calls for a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.52,0:24:52.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,今夜结束前 我也许就有继承人了\N{\rEng}I may have an heir before the night is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.39,0:24:57.26,Chs,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 请允许我介绍…德文郡六世公爵！\N{\rEng}Ladies and gentlemen, I give you the sixth Duke of Devonshire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.36,0:25:00.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,德文郡六世公爵！\N{\rEng}The sixth Duke of Devonshire!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.19,0:25:27.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 大人  - 我没心情谈话\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - I am in no mood for a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.12,0:25:29.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 大人  - 我没有心情说话\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - I am in no mood for a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.06,0:25:32.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,我祷告时问上帝 我的女儿能否…\N{\rEng}But, pray tell me, is my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.39,0:25:36.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,你的女儿能否给我生儿子？\N{\rEng}Is your daughter at all able to give me a son?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.20,0:25:37.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,别灰心 大人\N{\rEng}Take heart, Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.83,0:25:39.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,只要她身体康健 一定能生\N{\rEng}As long as the mother is in good health,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.60,0:25:41.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,就当这次失误是打草稿好了\N{\rEng}consider this mishap a draft,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.70,0:25:44.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,当成是将得贵子的保证\N{\rEng}a promise of what is soon to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.67,0:25:47.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 在我们家族…  - 我知道 在你们家\N{\rEng}- In our family, we...  - Yes, I know, in your family,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.47,0:25:49.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,在你们家\N{\rEng}in your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.31,0:25:53.68,Chs,,0,0,0,,大人 告退\N{\rEng}Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.85,0:26:00.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,看到光没有？看到没有？\N{\rEng}Can you see the light? Can you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.20,0:26:10.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你好么 亲爱的？ - 还好\N{\rEng}- Darling, how are you?  - Quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.17,0:26:16.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 她健康么 壮实么？ - 她十分完美\N{\rEng}- Is she strong and healthy?  - She's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.71,0:26:25.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 威廉他见你了没有？ - 见了\N{\rEng}- Did William receive you?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.18,0:26:29.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,她不是男孩 他很失望吧？\N{\rEng}Is he upset that she's not a son?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.12,0:26:35.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,他只看了她一眼就走了 之后就不见人影\N{\rEng}He just glanced at her and then left. I've hardly seen him since.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.59,0:26:37.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,亲爱的 大人现在也很不好受\N{\rEng}It's been a difficult time for His Grace, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.69,0:26:41.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,他现在是许多目光的焦点 其中有一些目光绝非善意\N{\rEng}Many eyes are upon him and not all of them kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.53,0:26:46.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,她真是太可爱了\N{\rEng}She is the loveliest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.04,0:26:51.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 保姆呢？ - 不用 我自己喂她\N{\rEng}- Nurse?  - No, I will feed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.57,0:26:53.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你真要喂她么？ - 是的\N{\rEng}- Are you sure, darling?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.98,0:27:02.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,即使是女孩 怎么说我也是她的母亲\N{\rEng}I am her mother, after all, even if she is only a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.05,0:27:06.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,来喽\N{\rEng}There.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.72,0:27:09.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,该死的混账！\N{\rEng}Hell and damnation!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.25,0:27:20.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,10)\fs38\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(973,480)\c&HD5E6E4&}六年之后
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.72,0:27:26.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,10)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(980,740)\c&HD5E6E4&}哈瑞尔 　　　　　　　　　　小乔　　 　　　　　　　　　夏洛特
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.55,0:27:51.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,10)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(980,770)\c&HD5E6E4&}巴斯镇
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.43,0:27:53.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,人在度假的时候\N{\rEng}It is always a pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.23,0:27:57.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,如能聆得一段奇智妙语 总是一桩乐事\N{\rEng}when one is on holiday to request a few words of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.24,0:27:58.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,在此我也不多费口舌了\N{\rEng}And so without further ado,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.94,0:28:03.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,下面郑重推出今晚最尊贵的客人\N{\rEng}it is a great honor to hand over to our most distinguished guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.74,0:28:06.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,这位贵客在场时 是所有目光的焦点\N{\rEng}When she arrives, all eyes are upon her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.88,0:28:10.91,Chs,,0,0,0,,不在场时 她依然是一切话题的中心\N{\rEng}When absent, she is the subject of universal conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.02,0:28:13.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,今晚她亮相时所穿的衣着\N{\rEng}And what we see her wearing tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.12,0:28:17.08,Chs,,0,0,0,,到了明天估计就会人手一件了\N{\rEng}I look forward to seeing the rest of you wearing tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.19,0:28:22.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,有请引领时尚的女皇 德文郡公爵夫人！\N{\rEng}The empress of fashion herself, the Duchess of Devonshire.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.61,0:28:34.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们来巴斯 是为了远离伦敦\N{\rEng}We come away to Bath to get away from London,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.34,0:28:36.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,谁知整个伦敦都跟着来了巴斯\N{\rEng}and all of London has come away to Bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.21,0:28:40.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,有人还真开口问过我\N{\rEng}Somebody did indeed ask me
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.11,0:28:42.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,我头上戴的是什么鸟的羽毛\N{\rEng}what kind of feather it is that I'm wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.72,0:28:46.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,据说这种珍奇的鸟类 一共只发现了两只\N{\rEng}Well, there are only two specimens of this rare bird known to man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.85,0:28:51.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,很显然其中一只已在我的头顶上安息了\N{\rEng}One of them has clearly ended up on top of my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.22,0:28:55.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,至于那另一只 传闻说已经跑到 托利党(该党支持世袭王权)的办公室去了\N{\rEng}And the other, rumor has it, is running for office in the Tory Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.09,0:29:21.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,贝丝·福斯特\N{\rEng}Bess Foster.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.53,0:29:33.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,请原谅\N{\rEng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.47,0:30:15.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我们还没有彼此介绍过  - 是还没有 我是伊丽莎白·福斯特夫人\N{\rEng}- I don't believe we've been introduced.  - No, we haven't. Lady Elizabeth Foster.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.31,0:30:19.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我刚才看见你和我丈夫说话来着  - 是的 他想请我跳舞\N{\rEng}- I saw you talking with my husband.  - Yes. He wanted to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.05,0:30:26.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,这可不是他的擅长啊 你拒绝了没有？\N{\rEng}That's not usually considered his forte. And you declined?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.29,0:30:30.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,我现在没兴致找男士作陪\N{\rEng}I'm ill at ease with male company for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.69,0:30:35.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.03,0:30:38.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,你为什么来巴斯？\N{\rEng}So what brings you to Bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.27,0:30:44.96,Chs,,0,0,0,,我丈夫正在伯恩茅斯与情人寻欢作乐\N{\rEng}My husband, Mr. Foster, is enjoying his mistress in Bournemouth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.07,0:30:48.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,我来这儿解解闷 你呢？\N{\rEng}and I wanted some diversion. And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.38,0:30:54.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵想借这儿的温泉治疗痛风\N{\rEng}The Duke is taking the waters for his gout.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.52,0:30:57.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我跟他一起来调养身体  - 真的？\N{\rEng}- And I for my health.  - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.65,0:31:02.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,我听说你们来这儿的原因是你无法育子\N{\rEng}I heard you were here because you could not conceive a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.16,0:31:06.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉 说这种话太失礼了\N{\rEng}I beg your pardon, that was an awful thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.59,0:31:08.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,至少这是事实\N{\rEng}It was the truth, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.39,0:31:11.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,请原谅我说傻话 我总是口没遮拦\N{\rEng}Trust me to say something silly. I always do, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.13,0:31:14.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,那你就该答应公爵的请求\N{\rEng}Then perhaps you should have accepted the Duke's offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.17,0:31:16.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,你们两个有许多共同点\N{\rEng}You have much in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.11,0:31:30.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们回去吧 乔治安娜\N{\rEng}Home, I think, Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.49,0:31:43.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你住在哪儿？ - 我在镇上租了几间房\N{\rEng}- Where are you staying?  - I've rented some rooms in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.26,0:31:46.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我们一定还会再见的  - 一定会的\N{\rEng}- We must meet again.  - We must.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.58,0:32:07.52,Chs,,0,0,0,,哈瑞儿 过来 到这儿来…摔疼了没有？\N{\rEng}Harryo. Come here. Come here. Did that hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.62,0:32:10.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 妈妈  - 我的小天使\N{\rEng}- Mama.  - My angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.12,0:32:15.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,疼不疼？那儿疼么？让我看看 是不是这只膝盖？\N{\rEng}Are you sore? Was that sore? Let me have a look. Was it this knee?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.83,0:32:18.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,没事 你不会死的\N{\rEng}I think you shall live.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.70,0:32:23.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,好了 看谁先跑到桥那里 听我口令 一 二 三…跑！\N{\rEng}Right. First to the bridge on my count. One, two, three. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.30,0:32:24.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,来啊 哈瑞儿\N{\rEng}Come on, Harryo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.64,0:32:27.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 不 我能赶上她的！ - 我要追上你！\N{\rEng}- No, I'm gonna catch her!  - I'm gonna catch you!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.91,0:32:32.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,跌倒爬起 跌倒爬起…为什么我们就不能恢复得那么快呢？\N{\rEng}Up and down. Up and down. Why can't we recover like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.21,0:32:34.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,因为我们在跌倒前 已经走了太长的路\N{\rEng}It's too far to fall now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.28,0:32:37.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 又见面了  - 你好 你的几个女儿真可爱\N{\rEng}- Hello again.  - Hello. Your girls are lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.88,0:32:42.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 你有孩子么？ - 有 三个男孩\N{\rEng}- Thank you. Do you have any children?  - I do. Three boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.82,0:32:45.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,三个男孩\N{\rEng}Three boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.73,0:32:48.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,要能分一个男孩给公爵 估计他什么都肯拿出来\N{\rEng}What the Duke wouldn't give for one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.33,0:32:57.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你的大女儿最不像你  - 是的 我想其中的故事你应该知道\N{\rEng}- She is least like you, your eldest.  - Yes. I'm sure you know the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.37,0:33:04.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,我丈夫的大女儿是在我们结婚前出世的\N{\rEng}My husband's daughter was born before we married.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.84,0:33:08.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,她的母亲是一名女仆 女仆死后 孩子就交给我们带了\N{\rEng}Her mother was a maid. The maid died, and we took the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.92,0:33:11.78,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 对不起 我又说了不该说的  - 没事\N{\rEng}- I'm sorry. Have I spoken out of turn?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.89,0:33:15.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,在伦敦 这是人尽皆知的秘密 她现在已经九岁了\N{\rEng}It's the worst-kept secret in London. She's nine years old now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.69,0:33:17.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,你爱她么？\N{\rEng}And you love her?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.52,0:33:20.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,当然爱 我对她视如己出\N{\rEng}Of course I do. The same as all my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.96,0:33:26.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,来 我给你介绍一下\N{\rEng}Come and meet them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.33,0:33:30.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,姑娘们 来认识一下妈妈的新朋友 伊丽莎白夫人\N{\rEng}Girls. Come and meet my new friend, Lady Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.81,0:33:40.44,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人 给你  - 谢谢…这是温泉水\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Thank you. Thermal water.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.48,0:33:44.38,Chs,,0,0,0,,那股怪味是因为里面有硫黄\N{\rEng}It's the sulfur that makes it smell so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.48,0:33:48.32,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你真的要把这个喝了？ - 每天两杯 连喝四周\N{\rEng}- And you really have to drink it?  - Twice a day for four weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.76,0:33:53.82,Chs,,0,0,0,,难道你相信自己真的不能生男孩？\N{\rEng}Do you have any reason to believe you cannot birth a male?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.93,0:33:57.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,流产前 我一直不信这个\N{\rEng}No. Except miscarriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.70,0:34:01.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,两个死胎 都是男孩\N{\rEng}Two stillbirths, both sons.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.87,0:34:06.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我也生了两个健康的女孩\N{\rEng}But two healthy girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.95,0:34:19.08,Chs,,0,0,0,,每个人都看着你\N{\rEng}Everybody is staring at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.26,0:34:28.56,Chs,,0,0,0,,你头颈后面是什么？贝丝？\N{\rEng}What's that on your neck? Bess?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.10,0:34:33.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,法律规定男人不能用棍子抽打妻子\N{\rEng}It's not illegal for a man to beat his wife with a stick
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.03,0:34:37.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,除非使用的棍子比他的拇指更细\N{\rEng}unless the stick is thicker than his thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.14,0:34:41.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,福斯特先生？他怎么能这么做！\N{\rEng}Mr. Foster? But he can't have done that!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.21,0:34:43.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,比起他对我做的其他事 这还不算最糟\N{\rEng}Well, considering what else he's done to me, that's not the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.91,0:34:45.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,还有什么更糟的事？\N{\rEng}What could possibly be worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.45,0:34:48.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,他带走了我的孩子 还不准我见他们\N{\rEng}He's taken my children. He won't let me see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.99,0:34:59.32,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 那你打算怎么办？ - 说实话 我已经无计可施了\N{\rEng}- And what do you propose to do?  - Really, I'm at my wits' end.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.73,0:35:03.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,法律站在福斯特先生一边\N{\rEng}The law supports Mr. Foster.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.50,0:35:09.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,那现在你打算去哪儿栖身？\N{\rEng}In the meantime, where shall you stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.60,0:35:12.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,继续租房 直到钱花光为止\N{\rEng}Continue lodging, till the money runs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.48,0:35:19.31,Chs,,0,0,0,,那这样吧 这方面我还能帮点忙\N{\rEng}Well, there, at least, I think I can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.65,0:35:28.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,威廉？明天我们就要离开这儿了\N{\rEng}William? We leave tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.89,0:35:36.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,伊丽莎白夫人的娘家在欧洲大陆\N{\rEng}And Lady Elizabeth doesn't have to meet her parents on the continent
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.20,0:35:38.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,她也不急着回去\N{\rEng}for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.50,0:35:43.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 她几乎没怎么去过伦敦  - 那倒是个遗憾\N{\rEng}- She hardly ever visits London at all.  - It's a pity, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.24,0:35:49.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,那什么 在伦敦她也没地方可住\N{\rEng}You see, she doesn't have anywhere to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.08,0:35:53.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,这倒是个问题\N{\rEng}Problem there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.22,0:36:00.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,那好 让她和我们一起住如何？先住上一阵再说\N{\rEng}Well, why doesn't she stay with us? For a while, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.09,0:36:04.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢您\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.00,0:36:12.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 太不可思议了  - 那是在爱尔兰的城堡\N{\rEng}- This is incredible.  - There's the castle in Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.93,0:36:18.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,博尔顿修道院 奇斯威克 伯灵顿 …哦 当然还有查茨沃思\N{\rEng}Bolton Abbey, Chiswick, Burlington and, why, in Chatsworth, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.34,0:36:21.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 那是当然  - 那一处比别处大得多\N{\rEng}- Of course.  - Which is much bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.44,0:36:23.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,但这儿更像家\N{\rEng}But this is more like home.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.38,0:36:30.91,Chs,,0,0,0,,有你在这儿 我说不出有多高兴\N{\rEng}I'm so glad you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.02,0:36:33.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,我还准备了一出很精彩的开场节目\N{\rEng}I've arranged a wonderful start to the season.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.02,0:36:41.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,要是我再试着跟你修好\N{\rEng}May all the plagues of marriage be doubled on me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.03,0:36:47.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,就让婚姻的不幸加倍降临在我的身上！\N{\rEng}if ever I try to be friends with you anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.33,0:36:49.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,要是这样就好了\N{\rEng}So much the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.44,0:36:56.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,不 不 夫人 你显然对我毫不关心\N{\rEng}No, no, madam. 'Tis evident you care not a pin for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.94,0:37:01.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,我当初娶你的时候准是发疯了\N{\rEng}And I, I was a madman to marry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.31,0:37:05.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,我当初嫁你的时候准是糊涂了\N{\rEng}And I'm sure I was a fool to marry you,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.75,0:37:09.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,一个看见女人就追的王老五\N{\rEng}an old dangling bachelor
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.99,0:37:14.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,五十岁了还是个光棍\N{\rEng}who was single at 50
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.33,0:37:18.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,只因为找不到肯嫁他的人！\N{\rEng}only because he never could meet with anyone who could have him!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.12,0:37:43.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,贝丝 这位是反对党领袖福克斯先生\N{\rEng}Bess, may I introduce Mr. Fox, leader of the Opposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.09,0:37:47.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 福克斯先生 这是伊丽莎白·福斯特夫人  - 福克斯先生\N{\rEng}- Mr. Fox, Lady Elizabeth Foster.  - Mr. Fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.59,0:37:51.69,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我的门生 查尔斯·格雷  - 格雷先生\N{\rEng}- My protege, Charles Grey.  - Mr. Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.80,0:37:53.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 格雷先生  - 夫人\N{\rEng}- Mr. Grey.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.53,0:37:55.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,他是我们年轻的新星\N{\rEng}He's our newest bright young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.07,0:37:59.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,刚从剑桥毕业不久 已经是国会成员了\N{\rEng}Scarcely out of Cambridge and already a member of Parliament.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.21,0:38:04.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我就知道你会有作为的  - 谢谢\N{\rEng}- I always felt you'd do well.  - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.14,0:38:06.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 福克斯先生  - 好的 伊丽莎白夫人\N{\rEng}- Mr. Fox.  - Yes, Lady Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.38,0:38:13.38,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 喜欢刚才的戏嘛？ - 坦白的说 不是很喜欢\N{\rEng}- Did you enjoy the play?  - I must confess, I did not entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.32,0:38:17.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,希望涉足政界的你…\N{\rEng}I hope that you've not lost your sense of humor
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.29,0:38:19.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 那份幽默感还没丢  - 据我所知还在\N{\rEng}- since entering politics.  - Not that I'm aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.96,0:38:21.55,Chs,,0,0,0,,那我想你应该知道\N{\rEng}Then I'm sure you realize that School for Scandal
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.66,0:38:24.69,Chs,,0,0,0,,-“造谣学校”这部戏是一部喜剧  - 我知道\N{\rEng}- was written as a comedy.  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.80,0:38:28.79,Chs,,0,0,0,,但就我观戏的感受 这好像是一出悲剧\N{\rEng}Although, from where I sat, it read as a tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.90,0:38:32.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵夫人！我们太想念您了\N{\rEng}Your Grace! How we have missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.94,0:38:33.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,您不在的时候\N{\rEng}In your absence,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.04,0:38:36.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,伦敦成了最最无聊的城市\N{\rEng}London has been reduced to the dreariest province.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.88,0:38:39.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,这位就是剧作家谢里顿先生\N{\rEng}And this, of course, is the playwright Mr. Sheridan.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.71,0:38:42.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,请允许我介绍伊丽莎白·福斯特夫人\N{\rEng}May I present the Lady Elizabeth Foster?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.11,0:38:43.24,Chs,,0,0,0,,恕我无礼\N{\rEng}I do not mean to be rude,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.35,0:38:45.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,剧组全体正翘首企盼公爵夫人的接见呢\N{\rEng}but I've an entire cast dying to meet the Duchess.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.62,0:38:48.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,去去就回 我保证\N{\rEng}I shall return you in a moment. Promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.16,0:38:52.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 福克斯先生？ - 嗯\N{\rEng}- Mr. Fox?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.23,0:38:53.25,Chs,,0,0,0,,借一句说话\N{\rEng}A word.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.36,0:38:57.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,让我上哪儿再去搜集这么多家庭琐事呢？\N{\rEng}Well, wherever do I glean such domestic gossip?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.10,0:39:01.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 这样做对公爵不太好吧？ - 我本来写的比这更夸张\N{\rEng}- Were we fair on the Duke?  - It could have been worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.30,0:39:04.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,原先的剧本标题是“糟糕的婚姻”\N{\rEng}My original title was The Bad Marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.97,0:39:10.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,他们一直都是这样的吗？\N{\rEng}Is it always like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.38,0:39:12.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,呃 正如他们所说\N{\rEng}Well, as they say,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.28,0:39:14.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,英格兰惟一不爱公爵夫人的男人\N{\rEng}the Duke of Devonshire must be the only man in England
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.61,0:39:16.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,就是德文郡公爵本人\N{\rEng}not in love with his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.38,0:39:20.68,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人 这位是德文郡公爵夫人  - 很高兴认识您\N{\rEng}- Her Grace, the Duchess of Devonshire.  - Very pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.53,0:39:32.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,刚才你有没有忘却旧愁 尽情享受？\N{\rEng}Were you at all able to forget things and enjoy yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.70,0:39:36.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,我玩得非常开心 谢谢你\N{\rEng}It was a wonderful distraction, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.74,0:39:37.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,那就好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.44,0:39:44.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 整晚我都在和格雷先生说话  - 是么？\N{\rEng}- I talked to Mr. Grey all evening.  - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.88,0:39:48.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,他正恋着你呢\N{\rEng}He's in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.48,0:39:53.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,亲爱的贝丝 我觉得他没有 恐怕情况恰好相反\N{\rEng}My dear Bess, no, he is not. Quite the reverse, I fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.65,0:39:57.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,他看你的那种方式 难道你看不出？\N{\rEng}Well, can't you tell by the way he looks at you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.46,0:40:00.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 说真的 你真觉察不到么？ - 别说了\N{\rEng}- Honestly, can't you tell?  - Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.90,0:40:07.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜 交媾并非只是为了生儿育女\N{\rEng}Georgiana, intercourse is not just about offspring.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.07,0:40:14.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 实际上 这是一件很有乐趣的事  - 是的 我懂\N{\rEng}- In fact, it can be rather pleasurable.  - Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.14,0:40:22.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,闭上眼睛 试着设想\N{\rEng}Close your eyes and try to envisage Grey
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.11,0:40:26.24,Chs,,0,0,0,,格雷正在解开你的衣裙 亲吻你的后背\N{\rEng}opening your dress, kissing your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.35,0:40:29.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 他们才不会这样做呢  - 不 他们会这么做\N{\rEng}- They never do such things.  - Yes, they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.00,0:40:38.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,把眼睛闭上\N{\rEng}Close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.14,0:40:48.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,格雷在你身后 慢慢褪去你的衣衫\N{\rEng}Grey is behind you slowly opening your dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.94,0:40:51.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 别这样 贝丝 快住手！ - 把眼睛闭上\N{\rEng}- No, Bess, stop!  - Close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.89,0:41:09.55,Chs,,0,0,0,,亲吻着你的背\N{\rEng}Kissing your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.55,0:41:33.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\rEng}There.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.99,0:41:36.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,明白了么？\N{\rEng}See?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.89,0:42:11.08,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 对不起 我离开一会儿  - 请原谅 先生们\N{\rEng}- Would you excuse me for a minute?  - You must excuse me, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.19,0:42:13.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人  - 格雷先生\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Mr. Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.73,0:42:16.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,还有六周就要全国大选了 对不对？\N{\rEng}The national election is in six weeks, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.46,0:42:18.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,竞选活动进展如何？\N{\rEng}How is the campaign going?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.37,0:42:22.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,很糟糕\N{\rEng}Terribly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.74,0:42:27.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们只希望福克斯能在西敏斯特留任\N{\rEng}Our only hope is to save Westminster for Fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.34,0:42:29.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,你应该也知道 我这人常犯错\N{\rEng}I have many faults, as you well know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.68,0:42:33.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,但至少在吸引注意力方面 我很在行\N{\rEng}Not least among them is my ability to draw attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.45,0:42:37.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,也许可以利用这一点为我方谋得利益\N{\rEng}Perhaps we could use that to our advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.37,0:42:55.16,Chs,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\N{\rEng}Ladies and gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.87,0:42:59.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 我要介绍一位先生\N{\rEng}Ladies and gentlemen, I give you the man
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.97,0:43:02.67,Chs,,0,0,0,,他将告诉我们 什么才是应该做的\N{\rEng}who will inform us of the work we must do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.78,0:43:07.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,哪个党才值得我们信任 有请查尔斯·格雷先生\N{\rEng}and of the party we so believe in. Mr. Charles Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.35,0:43:18.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,西敏斯特的好公民们！\N{\rEng}Good people of Westminster!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.82,0:43:24.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,这世界已走到灾难和浩劫的边缘！\N{\rEng}The world is on the brink of disaster or salvation!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.23,0:43:25.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,从法兰西到美利坚\N{\rEng}From France to America,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.00,0:43:28.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,从男人到女人 都在为自身自由而奋斗\N{\rEng}men and women are struggling to free themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.10,0:43:32.50,Chs,,0,0,0,,他们在寻找生存的真义！\N{\rEng}to find meaning in their existence!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.61,0:43:35.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,变革就在我们眼前！\N{\rEng}Change is upon us!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.58,0:43:40.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,不能再走回老路了\N{\rEng}We shall not go back to the old ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.38,0:43:45.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,让我们带领英格兰勇敢迈进新世界\N{\rEng}We shall take England into this brave new world
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.65,0:43:48.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,用一声惊雷震响整个天空！\N{\rEng}and shake the thunder from the skies!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.50,0:44:06.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我表现如何？ - 说不上令人难堪\N{\rEng}- How did I do?  - I think it was not an embarrassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.74,0:44:09.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,应该说非常精彩\N{\rEng}It was a marvel.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.08,0:44:14.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,我当时很紧张 您的大驾光临 使到场人数至少翻了三倍\N{\rEng}I was nervous. Your presence trebled the numbers at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.08,0:44:19.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,现在的我比刚才更加紧张\N{\rEng}I'm nervous even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.02,0:44:25.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果能赢下这场选举 执掌政权\N{\rEng}If we win this election, if we get the power,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.03,0:44:27.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,想想到时候我们会怎么做\N{\rEng}think what we will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.09,0:44:30.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们分开的时候 你会想我么？\N{\rEng}Do you think of me when we're not together?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.10,0:44:35.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,你该明白 那是肯定的\N{\rEng}You ought to know I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.70,0:44:38.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 在回答之前 你犹豫了  - 没有\N{\rEng}- You hesitated before you replied.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.15,0:44:50.78,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不太习惯面对如此直接的提问\N{\rEng}I'm unused to being asked so directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.19,0:44:56.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,这么多人里 偏偏是你来问我\N{\rEng}And by you, of all people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.33,0:45:03.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,我无时无刻不在想你 从未改变过\N{\rEng}I think of you all the time. I always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.44,0:45:13.43,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人 您的马车在等您  - 谢谢\N{\rEng}- Your carriage awaits, Your Grace.  - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.37,0:45:17.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,…我们发誓！\N{\rEng}...this we vow!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.10,0:45:48.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,你们在伊丽莎白夫人的卧室外做什么？\N{\rEng}What are you doing outside Lady Elizabeth's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.65,0:45:55.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,她和谁在里面？\N{\rEng}Who's in there with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.88,0:47:07.87,Chs,,0,0,0,,英格兰有那么多女人 你偏要把她压在身子下面\N{\rEng}Of all the women in England you had to throw yourself on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.09,0:47:17.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,你的风流韵事 我从没表示过反对\N{\rEng}I have never once objected to any of your affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.93,0:47:23.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,你安排的所有活动 我一概接受服从\N{\rEng}I have accepted whatever arrangement you have proposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.64,0:47:29.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,我还把夏洛特当作亲生女儿抚养\N{\rEng}I have raised Charlotte as my own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.34,0:47:33.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,但是这个…\N{\rEng}But this...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.81,0:47:40.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,好不容易才有一件属于自己的东西\N{\rEng}I have one single thing of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.19,0:47:47.38,Chs,,0,0,0,,为什么不能把伊丽莎白留给我呢？\N{\rEng}Why couldn't you let me keep Elizabeth for myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.79,0:47:52.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,你究竟算什么玩意儿啊？\N{\rEng}What kind of man are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.57,0:48:01.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,她是我婚姻生活中仅有的慰藉 你却把我唯一的朋友生生抢走！\N{\rEng}She is my sole comfort in our marriage. You have robbed me of my only friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:12.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,我有什么不对？\N{\rEng}What is wrong with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.01,0:48:39.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,我…\N{\rEng}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.11,0:48:47.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,我从不认为自己是个善解人意的男人\N{\rEng}I've never claimed to be a man of fine sensibility, G.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.58,0:48:50.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我一直清楚这桩婚姻应该给我什么\N{\rEng}But I've always known what I expect from this marriage
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.95,0:48:53.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,以及对此我该付出些什么\N{\rEng}and what I'm prepared to give.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.46,0:48:58.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,作为丈夫 我履行了应尽的义务\N{\rEng}As a husband, I have fulfilled my obligations.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.56,0:49:01.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,但是作为妻子\N{\rEng}But, as a wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.20,0:49:06.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,你却没有尽职尽责\N{\rEng}you have not.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.44,0:49:09.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,她必须离开 马上走\N{\rEng}She has to go. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.94,0:49:12.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,不许她再踏进这个家一步！\N{\rEng}She is never to set foot in this house again!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.64,0:49:14.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,请注意控制你的情绪 乔 你似乎忘记了自己的身份\N{\rEng}Do mind your temper, G. You're forgetting yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.05,0:49:17.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,我要她滚\N{\rEng}I want her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.82,0:49:24.55,Chs,,0,0,0,,我再也不想见到她 你下去跟她说 让她马上走\N{\rEng}I never want to lay eyes on her again. Go down and tell her to leave at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.16,0:49:31.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不会让她走的\N{\rEng}I couldn't ask her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.76,0:49:35.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不愿意这么做 乔\N{\rEng}I won't do it, G.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.68,0:49:57.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 第一眼见到她 我就不喜欢  - 你已经说过了 妈妈\N{\rEng}- I never liked her from the first. - You made that quite clear, Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.99,0:50:00.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,她已经不在公爵宅邸了吧\N{\rEng}She's gone from Devonshire House, I hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.79,0:50:06.79,Chs,,0,0,0,,他们现在住在一起？\N{\rEng}They're living there together?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.90,0:50:09.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜！你怎么能答应这种事情？\N{\rEng}Georgiana! What have you permitted to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.33,0:50:12.96,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不知道 我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.07,0:50:16.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,帮帮我 求你帮帮我 妈妈 告诉我应该怎么办\N{\rEng}Help me. Help me, please, Mama. Tell me what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.28,0:50:25.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,给你的丈夫写信 坚持让他把人送走\N{\rEng}You must write to your husband and insist he send her back
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.48,0:50:27.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,不管她原来住得多烂 哪儿来就回哪儿去\N{\rEng}to whatever horrid little place she came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.75,0:50:32.52,Chs,,0,0,0,,他不会照办的 他说过“你想都别想”\N{\rEng}He will not. "It is out of the question," he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.26,0:50:42.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,那你就回去 继续履行你的义务\N{\rEng}Then you must return and resume your duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.20,0:50:44.72,Chs,,0,0,0,,让他明白 谁才是他的真爱\N{\rEng}Make him realize whom he loves.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.83,0:50:47.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,把政治活动和赌博游戏先放一放\N{\rEng}You will give up your politics and your gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.70,0:50:51.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,你且专心做一回钟情的妻子\N{\rEng}For once, you will devote yourself as a loving wife
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.11,0:50:55.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,安心完成当前的要务 给他生个儿子\N{\rEng}and settle down to the task in hand, providing him with an heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.48,0:50:58.71,Chs,,0,0,0,,很快他就会厌倦那个女人\N{\rEng}Then he will soon tire of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.52,0:51:09.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,你别无选择\N{\rEng}You have no other option.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.46,0:51:49.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,你好 乔\N{\rEng}Hello, G.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.03,0:51:53.26,Chs,,0,0,0,,威廉\N{\rEng}William.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.70,0:52:30.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,我虽无权把你赶出大宅\N{\rEng}I may not have the authority to remove you from my house,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.81,0:52:33.43,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我至少可以命令你滚出我的房间\N{\rEng}but I can, at least, order you out of my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.54,0:52:35.91,Chs,,0,0,0,,能不能容我解释？\N{\rEng}Won't you please let me explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.51,0:52:38.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,没什么好解释的\N{\rEng}There is nothing to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.68,0:52:42.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,为了重新见到孩子 这是我唯一的机会\N{\rEng}This is my only chance of ever seeing my children again.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.45,0:52:45.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵他是英格兰最有权势的贵族\N{\rEng}The Duke is the most powerful peer in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.76,0:52:46.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,我只有他这一根救命稻草\N{\rEng}He is my only chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.09,0:52:51.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,为夺回孩子而做的牺牲也得有个限度\N{\rEng}There are limits to the sacrifices one makes for one's children.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.13,0:52:55.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,不对 根本不可能有限度\N{\rEng}No, there aren't. No limits whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.37,0:52:59.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,出去\N{\rEng}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.54,0:53:06.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们两个已经没什么可说的了\N{\rEng}We have nothing more to say to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.43,0:54:00.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,妈妈 妈妈！\N{\rEng}Mama, Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.17,0:54:10.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,能见到您太好了 妈妈\N{\rEng}It's so nice to see you, Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.84,0:54:13.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,没错 这是一把猎枪\N{\rEng}Right, this is a shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.51,0:54:15.44,Chs,,0,0,0,,你妈妈说你对枪很感兴趣 是不是？\N{\rEng}Your mother said you'd be interested, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.54,0:54:16.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.18,0:54:19.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,这是打火石 看见没有？\N{\rEng}This is a flint. Do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.98,0:54:23.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,打火石击中这儿之后 就会产生火花\N{\rEng}When the flint hits there, it causes a spark to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.12,0:54:28.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,然后火花会点燃火药 把子弹推出枪膛\N{\rEng}Now, the spark, it lights the gunpowder and sends the bullet out of the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.09,0:54:31.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你知道怎么拿枪么？ - 不知道 先生\N{\rEng}- Do you know how to hold it?  - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.33,0:54:36.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,是这么个拿法 把这东西顶在右肩上\N{\rEng}Well, it's like that. Tuck it in there, into your right shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.87,0:54:40.50,Chs,,0,0,0,,拿稳之后 把那只手往前挪一点\N{\rEng}Hold it firmly, then you can move that hand a little further along.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.60,0:54:44.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,感觉到它有多重了吗？身体得稍稍前倾\N{\rEng}Can you feel how heavy it is? You have to lean into it a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.74,0:54:48.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,睁大双眼 顺着枪管看前方\N{\rEng}And keep both eyes open. Look right along the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.81,0:54:51.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,就像这样 看着前面\N{\rEng}Right along there just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.15,0:54:57.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,砰！来 我示范给你看\N{\rEng}Bang! Here, let me show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.76,0:55:02.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,瞧那儿\N{\rEng}There.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.99,0:55:05.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,枪很沉 对不对？\N{\rEng}It's quite heavy, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.46,0:55:10.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,你口干么？要不要喝点东西？\N{\rEng}Are you thirsty? Would you like something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.57,0:55:14.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,各位先生口渴么？要不要喝点什么？\N{\rEng}Are you gentlemen thirsty? Would you like something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.34,0:55:17.67,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.49,0:56:13.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵知道你要和谁见面吗？\N{\rEng}Did you tell the Duke who you were meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.73,0:56:14.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,不知道\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.63,0:56:17.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 他没问过？ - 没有\N{\rEng}- Did he even ask?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.70,0:56:20.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,他的脑子在想别的事\N{\rEng}He has other things on his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.57,0:56:23.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,你也一样\N{\rEng}As do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.41,0:56:30.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,向我倾诉心事 能不能让你好受一些？\N{\rEng}Would it help to unburden yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.65,0:56:36.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,我没什么能向你倾诉的\N{\rEng}It's nothing I can discuss with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.05,0:56:40.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,而且 说这些只会令人厌烦\N{\rEng}Besides, it would only bore.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.09,0:56:44.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,你没必要总想着让别人好受\N{\rEng}You don't have to please others all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.13,0:56:48.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,从小到大 我一直在学如何让别人好受 要忘却这些东西 很难\N{\rEng}It's what I've been brought up to do. Difficult lesson to unlearn.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.73,0:56:54.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,允许我发表几句评论么？\N{\rEng}Would you permit me an observation?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.51,0:57:01.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,我觉得你这么做 是为了让别人喜欢你\N{\rEng}I believe you do it so that people will love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.48,0:57:05.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 这么说有什么根据呢？ - 根据本人的所见所闻\N{\rEng}- What makes you say that?  - From what I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.28,0:57:12.31,Chs,,0,0,0,,你的丈夫 你的朋友 特别是贝丝夫人…\N{\rEng}With your husband, your friends, especially Lady Bess,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.56,0:57:16.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,连大众也是一样\N{\rEng}even the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.29,0:57:20.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,我以前从没这么想过\N{\rEng}I never thought of it that way before.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.87,0:57:25.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,你让我觉得自己更加可悲了\N{\rEng}You make me sound so pitiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.94,0:57:32.24,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜\N{\rEng}Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.48,0:57:38.24,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不该无礼多嘴 向你道歉\N{\rEng}I've gone beyond my brief. I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.15,0:57:43.55,Chs,,0,0,0,,请相信我 说这些都是为了你好\N{\rEng}Please believe it was only for your sake that I spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.85,0:57:47.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,求求你告诉我 究竟是哪儿不对\N{\rEng}Please, tell me what is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.66,0:57:55.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,我怕有些事自己做得太迟\N{\rEng}I fear I've done some things in life too late
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.60,0:57:57.43,Chs,,0,0,0,,而有些事来得又太早\N{\rEng}and others too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.07,0:58:03.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,不 你没有\N{\rEng}No, you haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.26,0:58:20.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉\N{\rEng}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.59,0:58:59.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.61,0:59:17.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.28,0:59:22.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,什么“好吧”？\N{\rEng}"All right"?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.19,0:59:28.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,你们俩彼此相爱么？\N{\rEng}Do you love each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.83,0:59:34.96,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 乔治安娜…  - 大人 您爱贝丝吗？\N{\rEng}- Georgiana...  - Do you love Bess, Your Grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.63,0:59:40.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你究竟想说什么？ - 我对他没有要求\N{\rEng}- Where is all this leading?  - I make no demands on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.47,0:59:46.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 那你呢贝丝 你爱我丈夫吗？ - 爱他就和爱你一样多\N{\rEng}- And, Bess, do you love my husband?  - As I do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.61,0:59:51.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,这么说你想留在这里？\N{\rEng}And so you intend to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.68,0:59:56.78,Chs,,0,0,0,,威廉要我留在这里\N{\rEng}William has asked that I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.19,1:00:01.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,你的内心就没想过要拒绝他？\N{\rEng}You couldn't find it in your heart to refuse him?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.59,1:00:04.68,Chs,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.03,1:00:10.96,Chs,,0,0,0,,那我们做一笔交易吧\N{\rEng}Then let us make a deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.90,1:00:14.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 一笔交易？ - 是的\N{\rEng}- A deal?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.37,1:00:20.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,我愿意成全你们两个\N{\rEng}I give you my blessing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.68,1:00:24.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,只要你肯接受我对查尔斯·格雷的感情\N{\rEng}if you will accept my feelings for Charles Grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.08,1:00:28.67,Chs,,0,0,0,,一开始我没意识到\N{\rEng}I didn't realize it at first.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.78,1:00:32.31,Chs,,0,0,0,,我以为那也许只是逢场作戏\N{\rEng}I thought that perhaps it was only a dalliance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.79,1:00:35.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,和他在一起能让我快乐\N{\rEng}It can make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.50,1:00:43.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,一笔交易？一笔交易\N{\rEng}A deal? A deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.87,1:00:46.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,我从不做什么交易\N{\rEng}I don't make deals.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.77,1:00:49.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,有这必要么？\N{\rEng}Why would I?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.74,1:00:52.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,我掌控着一切\N{\rEng}I'm in charge of it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.04,1:00:57.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,我可以把他约出来 然后责问他\N{\rEng}You know, I would call him out. I would challenge him.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.71,1:00:59.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我会用子弹射穿他的脑袋  - 威廉\N{\rEng}- I'd put a bullet in his head.  - William.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.45,1:01:03.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,别说话 你铁了心 想让我变成别人的笑柄？\N{\rEng}Be quiet. Are you determined to make me a total laughingstock?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.65,1:01:06.38,Chs,,0,0,0,,给一个无法续嗣的男人再戴一顶绿帽子？\N{\rEng}A man who cannot sire a son, and then a cuckold?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.49,1:01:08.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,威廉 乔治安娜只想问问我们…\N{\rEng}William. Georgiana only asks what we ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.76,1:01:10.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,不许说话 婊子！\N{\rEng}Be quiet, woman!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.49,1:01:15.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你跟他苟且了？ - 没有\N{\rEng}- Are you his whore?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.33,1:01:18.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,我也不明白 你为什么如此介意\N{\rEng}But I can't see why you'd mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.60,1:01:22.00,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你已经有贝丝和三个儿子了！ - 三个儿子？\N{\rEng}- You have Bess and three boys!  - Three boys?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.21,1:01:27.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,你说我会认那些个小杂种做继承人嘛？\N{\rEng}Do you think I can make those bastards my heirs?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.14,1:01:30.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,嗯？你说说看？\N{\rEng}Well? Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.16,1:01:42.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,威廉！\N{\rEng}William!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.69,1:02:16.68,Chs,,0,0,0,,你压根就不了解我 是不是？\N{\rEng}You don't know me in the least, do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.79,1:02:18.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,不 我了解你 我们完全不合拍\N{\rEng}Yes, I do. We're a bad match.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.69,1:02:22.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,结婚时我对你只有两个要求：忠贞和后嗣\N{\rEng}I asked but two things when we wed, loyalty and a male heir.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.00,1:02:25.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,和你对狗的要求有什么两样！\N{\rEng}The same as your dogs!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.51,1:02:33.50,Chs,,0,0,0,,不 不许碰我！别碰我！\N{\rEng}No, don't touch me! Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.55,1:02:37.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,走开！\N{\rEng}Get off!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.69,1:02:45.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,放开我！\N{\rEng}Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.59,1:02:49.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,你就是这样对她的？你就是这样对待那个娼妇的？\N{\rEng}Is this how you treat her? Is this how you treat your whore?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.03,1:02:52.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,不！不！\N{\rEng}No! No!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.23,1:02:56.25,Chs,,0,0,0,,不！不！不！\N{\rEng}No! No! No!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.13,1:02:58.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,不！\N{\rEng}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.57,1:03:05.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,来 夏洛特 跟我走\N{\rEng}Come with me. Charlotte, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.34,1:03:07.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,不！不！\N{\rEng}No! No!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.57,1:03:36.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,给我生个儿子 在此之前 呆在这里 按我说的去做\N{\rEng}Give me a son. Until then, stay here and do as I say.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.29,1:03:59.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,下面有请本次的赢家—福克斯先生 民众的宠儿！\N{\rEng}I give you the winner. Mr. Fox, the man of the people!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.10,1:04:11.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,我要请出的是我们的秘密武器 德文郡公爵夫人\N{\rEng}And I give you the weapon, the Duchess of Devonshire.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.99,1:04:25.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.69,1:04:30.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,在场的所有人 谢谢你们 今天能来参加我的欢迎会\N{\rEng}Thank you, all of you, for this reception today.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.23,1:04:38.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们今天赢了选举 明天我们将勾画未来！\N{\rEng}Today we have won the vote. Tomorrow we define the future!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.88,1:04:52.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 大人  - 大人\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.39,1:04:58.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 大人  - 大人\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.96,1:05:03.25,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\rEng}Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.36,1:05:10.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人  - 夫人\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.49,1:05:34.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人能赏光与在下跳一支舞么？\N{\rEng}Will Your Grace give me the favor of a dance?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.18,1:05:59.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,小心 乔\N{\rEng}Steady, G.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.32,1:06:06.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 着火了！ - 乔治安娜！\N{\rEng}- Fire!  - Georgiana!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.92,1:06:08.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人！\N{\rEng}Your Grace!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.46,1:06:10.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人的头发！\N{\rEng}Her Grace's hair!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.93,1:06:15.26,Chs,,0,0,0,,别愣着！\N{\rEng}Do something!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.04,1:06:29.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,请把夫人发套上的火给灭了\N{\rEng}Please put out Her Grace's hair.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.18,1:07:07.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人需要休息\N{\rEng}Her Grace needs to rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.32,1:07:09.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果严遵医嘱\N{\rEng}As long as she follows strict instructions
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.48,1:07:12.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人生产时应该不会有什么大碍\N{\rEng}there should be no impediment to the birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.55,1:07:14.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,你说什么？\N{\rEng}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.59,1:07:17.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵夫人有孕在身\N{\rEng}The Duchess is pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.96,1:07:50.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,还有这个\N{\rEng}And there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.66,1:07:55.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 希顿\N{\rEng}Thank you, Heaton.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.20,1:08:00.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,进来\N{\rEng}Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.58,1:08:13.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\rEng}Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.58,1:08:20.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,根据夫人的有关继承条款 这个给您\N{\rEng}As per the terms of His Grace's inheritance, this is for you
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.19,1:08:22.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,您可自由支配\N{\rEng}to spend as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.66,1:08:29.29,Chs,,0,0,0,,终于成功了\N{\rEng}Success at last.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.01,1:08:39.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜\N{\rEng}Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.61,1:08:44.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,其实这件事情 我也很厌恶\N{\rEng}I, too, abhor this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.10,1:09:05.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,再要一张 还是不要了？\N{\rEng}Twist or stick?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.07,1:09:09.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 不要了  - 不要了？\N{\rEng}- Stick.  - Stick?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.34,1:09:12.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,那我也不要了\N{\rEng}I'll stick, too, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.08,1:09:15.44,Chs,,0,0,0,,现在亮牌\N{\rEng}Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.31,1:09:18.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,你赢了 干得漂亮\N{\rEng}You won. Well done.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.11,1:09:20.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,驾\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.02,1:09:24.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,驾\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.25,1:09:27.31,Chs,,0,0,0,,驾\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.16,1:09:35.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,妈妈 你忘记摸牌了\N{\rEng}Mama, you forgot to deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.72,1:09:57.21,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人  - 格雷先生\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - Mr. Grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.25,1:10:02.31,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你从法兰西被召回了？ - 是暂时的\N{\rEng}- You are recalled from France?  - For a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.42,1:10:04.05,Chs,,0,0,0,,革命还没开始？\N{\rEng}No revolution yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.53,1:10:08.39,Chs,,0,0,0,,还没开始 但这只是时间问题\N{\rEng}No, not yet, but it's only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.07,1:10:15.16,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么会来这里？ - 我收到了一封请柬\N{\rEng}- How is it you are here?  - I received an invitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.01,1:10:21.14,Chs,,0,0,0,,我想大概是党内的事 不好拒绝\N{\rEng}I assumed it was on behalf of the Party. I could not say no.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.28,1:10:22.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,那是当然\N{\rEng}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.95,1:10:31.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,我生了一个儿子\N{\rEng}I bore a son.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.22,1:10:35.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,是嘛\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.66,1:10:41.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,他名叫威廉·乔治·斯宾塞·卡文迪什\N{\rEng}His name is William George Spencer Cavendish,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.33,1:10:46.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,哈廷顿侯爵 我们都叫他哈特\N{\rEng}Marquis of Hartington. We call him Hart.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.13,1:10:48.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,你和公爵一定很高兴吧\N{\rEng}You and the Duke must be very pleased.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.50,1:10:49.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}We are.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.74,1:10:56.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,公爵去伦敦举行欢庆仪式了\N{\rEng}The Duke has gone to London to celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.55,1:11:04.31,Chs,,0,0,0,,很想念你\N{\rEng}You have been missed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.26,1:11:08.69,Chs,,0,0,0,,非常非常想念\N{\rEng}Much missed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.93,1:11:18.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 十个筹码押皇后  - 四个筹码押五点\N{\rEng}- Ten on the Queen.  - Four on five.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.17,1:11:20.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,下注时间结束\N{\rEng}And no more bets, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.14,1:11:26.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,四点输了\N{\rEng}The losing card, four.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.31,1:11:32.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,皇后赢了\N{\rEng}The winning card, Queen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.34,1:12:00.74,Chs,,0,0,0,,很好 八个筹码押三点\N{\rEng}Jolly good. Eight on the three.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.84,1:12:02.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,押五个筹码在五点上\N{\rEng}Put five on the five.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.68,1:12:06.91,Chs,,0,0,0,,押五点的还没赢过呢 乔\N{\rEng}All of the fives have gone, G.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.22,1:12:12.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,我太累了 不想玩了\N{\rEng}I think I'm too tired to play.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.49,1:12:17.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 先生们 告退  - 夫人慢走\N{\rEng}- Gentlemen.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.70,1:12:31.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜\N{\rEng}Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.94,1:12:34.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,别让任何人知道\N{\rEng}No one must know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.01,1:12:38.81,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 格雷是你请来的啊  - 晚安\N{\rEng}- You summoned Grey.  - Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.83,1:14:42.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,我打算去一趟巴斯\N{\rEng}I was thinking about going to Bath.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.41,1:14:52.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,贝丝 这次我去疗养 你就待在这儿 陪着我们的丈夫吧\N{\rEng}Bess, you can stay here and look after our husband whilst I take the cure.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.72,1:14:57.08,Chs,,0,0,0,,好啊…你说呢 威廉？\N{\rEng}Yes, William. Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.19,1:15:00.78,Chs,,0,0,0,,让乔先去 等你有空了 我们再去那儿和她会合\N{\rEng}If G goes now, we can catch up with her when you're free.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.99,1:15:03.69,Chs,,0,0,0,,既然你坚持 那就这样吧\N{\rEng}Well, if you must.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.30,1:15:16.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}《巴斯新闻报》
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.77,1:15:20.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,“昨天 德文郡公爵夫人 戴着花边高帽来到了巴斯”\N{\rEng}"The Duchess of Devonshire appeared last week in Bath in a mobcap.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.94,1:15:25.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,“夫人自从投身竞选事业之后…”\N{\rEng}"Her Grace, ever since initiation into the business of electioneering,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.28,1:15:27.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,“似乎更钟情花边高帽了”\N{\rEng}"has been much attached to the mobs."
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.25,1:15:28.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,很好嘛\N{\rEng}Very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.59,1:15:34.82,Chs,,0,0,0,,你最喜欢哪一个？\N{\rEng}So which one is your favorite?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.03,1:15:40.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 看这张  - 嗯\N{\rEng}- This one.  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.46,1:15:45.69,Chs,,0,0,0,,这张图里的你似乎手气不错 终于连胜了几把\N{\rEng}In this one it seems you've hit a winning streak, for once.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.80,1:15:47.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,不错啊\N{\rEng}Very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.97,1:15:52.50,Chs,,0,0,0,,这张图里的你…\N{\rEng}And in this one you see...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.61,1:15:56.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,穿这样的裙子很适合吸引投票者啊\N{\rEng}Is that dress really an appropriate way to attract voters?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.51,1:15:59.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,你们这帮政客 根本不懂什么是时尚\N{\rEng}You politicians know absolutely nothing about fashion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.45,1:16:04.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果你真想问我最喜欢哪一个\N{\rEng}But if you were to really ask me which my favorite was,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.69,1:16:08.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,那就是我面前的这一个\N{\rEng}I'd say it was this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.27,1:16:25.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 早上好 查尔斯  - 早上好\N{\rEng}- Morning, Charles.  - Morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.47,1:16:26.91,Chs,,0,0,0,,祝您愉快 先生\N{\rEng}Good day to you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.57,1:16:55.23,Chs,,0,0,0,,很完美 谢谢你\N{\rEng}It's perfect. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.76,1:17:23.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们想给你一个惊喜 乔\N{\rEng}Thought we would surprise you, G.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.26,1:17:26.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,我记得你曾经说过 在你我的婚姻中自发的东西太少\N{\rEng}I think you once said there wasn't enough spontaneity in our marriage
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.20,1:17:28.17,Chs,,0,0,0,,或者类似意思的话\N{\rEng}or words to that effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.71,1:17:33.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,妈妈 你来这里干嘛？\N{\rEng}Mama, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.58,1:17:39.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,你在巴斯 应该见了不少朋友吧\N{\rEng}So, have you seen many of our circle in Bath?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.72,1:17:42.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,见了一些\N{\rEng}Some.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.15,1:17:49.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,寇克斯家族 哈沃福德 维克罗勋爵\N{\rEng}The Cokes and Haverford and Lord Wicklow.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.59,1:17:53.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,也见了不少政客吧？开会之类的\N{\rEng}Bunch of politicos, too, aren't there? Meetings and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.13,1:17:55.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,我想是吧\N{\rEng}I believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.23,1:17:59.67,Chs,,0,0,0,,格雷他来了没有？我说的是查尔斯·格雷先生\N{\rEng}Is Grey here? By which I mean Mr. Charles Grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.60,1:18:02.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,听说他也在这儿\N{\rEng}Rumor has it that he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.84,1:18:04.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我不会放弃他的  - 乔治安娜\N{\rEng}- I won't give him up.  - Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.67,1:18:07.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,人人都有情人 贝丝就是我丈夫的情人\N{\rEng}Everyone has a lover. Bess is the lover of my husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.94,1:18:09.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果你还有判断力的话\N{\rEng}If you had shown some discretion,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.71,1:18:12.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 事情就不至于此  - 不至于此？\N{\rEng}- it might have been different.  - Different?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.21,1:18:14.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,不幸中的万幸是 这事还没被捅到报纸上\N{\rEng}The only good fortune is it hasn't yet made it to the papers.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.75,1:18:18.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,亲爱的 格雷他还是单身 没钱没地位\N{\rEng}My dear, Grey is unmarried. He has no wealth, no rank.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.69,1:18:22.12,Chs,,0,0,0,,这桩丑闻于他丝毫无损 所有的危险都在你这边\N{\rEng}He risks nothing with this affair. The hazard is all yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.22,1:18:25.06,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 格雷他爱我  - 威廉也爱你\N{\rEng}- Grey loves me.  - So does William.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.16,1:18:28.56,Chs,,0,0,0,,没错 我爱你\N{\rEng}Yes. I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.20,1:18:31.43,Chs,,0,0,0,,怎么个爱法？\N{\rEng}How?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.23,1:18:35.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,用我所理解的方式来表达爱\N{\rEng}In the way I understand love.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.87,1:18:43.57,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜 你闹得太过火了 此事有损我们的尊严\N{\rEng}Georgiana, this has gone much too far. It is beneath our dignity.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.68,1:18:46.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 伦敦上下都在谈论  - 让他们说去吧\N{\rEng}- All London is talking.  - Let them talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.15,1:18:48.67,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果是格雷让我变得堕落 那正好\N{\rEng}If Grey makes me a fallen woman, well and good.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.78,1:18:51.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,威廉就能和我离婚 让贝丝做德文郡公爵夫人\N{\rEng}Now William may divorce me and Bess becomes Duchess of Devonshire.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.39,1:18:53.25,Chs,,0,0,0,,这事决不可能发生\N{\rEng}That will never happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.46,1:18:57.79,Chs,,0,0,0,,这事还是由你自己去解决吧\N{\rEng}I think I will leave you to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.33,1:19:05.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,接下来呢？\N{\rEng}What follows now?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.63,1:19:08.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,你是不是会扯掉我的衣服 再在我的身上施一次淫威？\N{\rEng}Are you going to tear my clothes off and force yourself upon me again?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.00,1:19:11.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,我为什么要那么做？\N{\rEng}Why on earth would I do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.11,1:19:17.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,对我的举止和才智 你从来没尊重过\N{\rEng}I know that you've never thought much of my manners or my intellect, G.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.45,1:19:22.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,但事实上 我从不做毫无意义的事情\N{\rEng}But, in fact, I never do anything that serves no purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.72,1:19:25.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,我非常清楚你们两个发生了什么\N{\rEng}I know precisely what you two have together.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.69,1:19:27.52,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我们彼此相爱  - 对此我毫不怀疑\N{\rEng}- We love each other.  - I do not doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.62,1:19:29.32,Chs,,0,0,0,,他和你一样 是个理想主义者\N{\rEng}He is a dreamer like yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.42,1:19:34.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,你们俩都在幻想另一个虚幻的世界 那世界非但不存在 以后也不会有\N{\rEng}and you both dream of another world that does not exist and it never will.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.13,1:19:37.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,现实是什么样 还是让我来开导你吧\N{\rEng}As for reality, allow me to enlighten you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.97,1:19:42.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果你不肯立即放弃这个男人\N{\rEng}If you do not give him up at once, I will see to it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.87,1:19:47.33,Chs,,0,0,0,,我定会让他在这个国家无家可归 一文不名\N{\rEng}that every home and every checkbook in this country is closed to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.44,1:19:50.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,无论是国会厅前还是相府帏后\N{\rEng}He will be welcomed neither in the halls of government
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.38,1:19:52.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,他都会被扫地出门\N{\rEng}nor in its backrooms of power.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.08,1:19:55.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,他立志成为首相的梦想\N{\rEng}His dream of becoming prime minister
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.02,1:20:02.35,Chs,,0,0,0,,还有你们改变世界的共同心愿 全都会灰飞烟灭\N{\rEng}and your mutual fantasy of a changed world will be dead as ash.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.33,1:20:09.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,你也别想再见到你的孩子了\N{\rEng}And you will never see your children again.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.71,1:20:20.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜\N{\rEng}Georgiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.42,1:21:07.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,我请您即回伦敦\N{\rEng}I must ask you to return to London.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.86,1:21:09.82,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 你不走？ - 嗯\N{\rEng}- Without you?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.33,1:21:20.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,这些是我们女儿写的\N{\rEng}These are from our girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.84,1:21:25.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,小哈特还不会写字 当然了 他还不满一岁\N{\rEng}Little Hart neglected to write, but then, of course, he's not yet one.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.62,1:21:40.58,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 这将是你一生最大的错误  - 错了\N{\rEng}- This will be the mistake of your life.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.09,1:21:45.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,许多年之前 我就已经犯过了\N{\rEng}I made that many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.30,1:21:50.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,我相信你自己能出去\N{\rEng}I trust you can see yourself out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.05,1:22:13.89,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 该死的 快把门打开！ - 大人\N{\rEng}- Damn you, man, open the door!  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.27,1:24:15.27,Chs,,0,0,0,,妈妈 妈妈 妈妈 妈妈！\N{\rEng}Mama, Mama, Mama, Mama!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.85,1:24:21.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,妈妈 妈妈 妈妈\N{\rEng}Mama, Mama, Mama.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.13,1:24:43.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 走吧 姑娘们  - 我爱你 妈妈\N{\rEng}- Come on, girls.  - Mama. I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.57,1:24:47.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,快点 姑娘们 妈妈很快就会出来的\N{\rEng}Girls, run along. Your mother will join you in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.47,1:24:48.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,快点\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.85,1:24:53.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,走吧\N{\rEng}Run along.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.62,1:24:58.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔\N{\rEng}G.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.93,1:25:14.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,你我终于达成了协议\N{\rEng}You must know how greatly pleased I am
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.80,1:25:17.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,你知道我有多高兴么\N{\rEng}that we have come to an arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.94,1:25:22.03,Chs,,0,0,0,,小孩子离开母亲太久了 对她们可不好\N{\rEng}It's not good for little ones to be without their mother for so long.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.14,1:25:25.81,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 为了这 就要赔上我的一生  - 有个解决的办法\N{\rEng}- My life for theirs.  - That's one way of putting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.48,1:25:32.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,你妈妈把这叫做“个人满足之前的习惯礼数”\N{\rEng}Your mother called it "common decency before personal gratification,"
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.62,1:25:35.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,或者类似的话 具体形容我记不清了\N{\rEng}or some such thing. The exact words escape me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.56,1:25:39.25,Chs,,0,0,0,,是不是“监禁在自己的家中”？\N{\rEng}How about "imprisoned in my own house"?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.96,1:25:44.62,Chs,,0,0,0,,不是 她不是这么说的\N{\rEng}No. That's not how she put it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.57,1:25:48.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果是这种说法 我会记得的\N{\rEng}I would have remembered that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.33,1:26:14.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜！\N{\rEng}Georgiana!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.06,1:26:17.90,Chs,,0,0,0,,放开我！\N{\rEng}Unhand me!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.00,1:26:19.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜！\N{\rEng}Georgiana!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.07,1:26:26.94,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜！你能不能放手？\N{\rEng}Georgiana! Will you please unhand me?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.04,1:26:28.37,Chs,,0,0,0,,请原谅\N{\rEng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.55,1:26:38.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜！求求你\N{\rEng}Georgiana! Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.82,1:26:41.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,乔治安娜！\N{\rEng}Georgiana!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.72,1:26:45.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 伯利  - 放开他\N{\rEng}- Thank you, Burleigh.  - Let him go.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.03,1:26:52.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,我每天写十几封信 可你一封都没回\N{\rEng}I have written a dozen times a day. Still, there is nothing from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.83,1:26:56.36,Chs,,0,0,0,,出什么事了？难道你不再爱我了？\N{\rEng}What has happened? Do you love me no longer?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.84,1:27:02.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我对你的感觉没有改变  - 那我们就应该在一起\N{\rEng}- My personal feelings remain unaltered.  - Then we must be together again.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.38,1:27:04.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,我要娶你 要你为我生儿育女\N{\rEng}I want to marry you. I want you to bear my children.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.08,1:27:06.77,Chs,,0,0,0,,生的是男还是女 我不在乎！\N{\rEng}And I don't care if they're boys or girls!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.88,1:27:10.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 要能像你说的就好了  - 当然能 一定会的\N{\rEng}- I wish it could be that way.  - It can. It will.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.52,1:27:13.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,这一路总会有艰难苦痛\N{\rEng}Sorrows will come however we try to avoid them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.65,1:27:15.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们必须坚持到底 决不让步\N{\rEng}We must stay the course and never give in.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.99,1:27:18.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 不 查尔斯  - 离开这儿 跟我走\N{\rEng}- No, Charles.  - You must leave and be with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.86,1:27:21.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,做个自由的女人 走吧！我们现在就走！\N{\rEng}A free woman. Now! Let us leave now!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.13,1:27:23.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不能丢下我的孩子\N{\rEng}I cannot abandon my children.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.13,1:27:29.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,自己好好想想 你刚才叫我做的事\N{\rEng}Listen to what you are asking me to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.99,1:28:26.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,怎么了？这鸽子不对你的口味？\N{\rEng}What's the matter? Don't like the pigeon?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.86,1:28:30.73,Chs,,0,0,0,,我觉得还满好吃的\N{\rEng}I find it quite decent.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.41,1:28:41.07,Chs,,0,0,0,,我肚里怀着查尔斯·格雷的孩子\N{\rEng}I'm carrying Charles Grey's child.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.39,1:28:57.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,请把我的决定告诉公爵夫人\N{\rEng}Please be so kind as to inform the Duchess of my decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.03,1:29:02.26,Chs,,0,0,0,,事情安排如下\N{\rEng}This is how it will be.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.36,1:29:06.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,你会被带到乡下 在那儿生下孩子\N{\rEng}You will be taken to the country where you will give birth to the child,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.40,1:29:10.50,Chs,,0,0,0,,孩子将交给查尔斯·格雷的家人 由其抚养\N{\rEng}and the child will be trusted to the care of Charles Grey's family.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.64,1:29:16.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,你听见了吗？\N{\rEng}Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.31,1:29:19.30,Chs,,0,0,0,,她应该都听到了 我们走吧\N{\rEng}I think she's heard you. Let's leave her.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.41,1:29:21.40,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 乔治安娜 回答我  - 我说了 我们走\N{\rEng}- Georgiana, please.  - I said let's leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.55,1:29:23.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,这不是商量 我的决定她已经知道了\N{\rEng}This is not a discussion. She's been informed of my decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.05,1:29:26.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 给她一点同情吧 威廉  - 要什么同情啊\N{\rEng}- Have pity on her, William.  - Pity be damned.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.12,1:29:28.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,你也清楚 这是她自找的\N{\rEng}She's brought this upon herself, as well you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.56,1:29:31.55,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 走吧  - 不 我和她一起去\N{\rEng}- Now come.  - No. I will go with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.66,1:29:34.22,Chs,,0,0,0,,你哪儿也不准去\N{\rEng}But you're not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.33,1:29:36.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果乔要我去 我就跟她走\N{\rEng}I will go with G, if G will have me,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.13,1:29:39.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,你说什么做什么都没用 阻拦不了我们\N{\rEng}and there's nothing you can do or say to stop either of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.39,1:30:36.98,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你来陪我  - 我一定得陪在你身边\N{\rEng}- Thank you for coming.  - I couldn't not be with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.56,1:31:15.93,Chs,,0,0,0,,该动身了\N{\rEng}It's time.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.23,1:31:22.86,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 要不要…  - 不用 我来抱她\N{\rEng}- Would it help...  - No, I must take her.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.29,1:32:49.59,Chs,,0,0,0,,夫人 我是格雷将军\N{\rEng}Your Grace, I'm General Grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.46,1:32:54.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,查尔斯在哪儿？\N{\rEng}Where's Charles?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.93,1:32:58.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,你丈夫觉得这事最好由我出面\N{\rEng}Your husband thought it best if I took care of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.97,1:33:37.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,格雷将军\N{\rEng}General Grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.17,1:33:41.83,Chs,,0,0,0,,她的名字是伊莱莎\N{\rEng}Her name is Eliza.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.85,1:33:55.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.60,1:34:11.54,Chs,,0,0,0,,好了 乔 抱着我 抱着我\N{\rEng}Come on, G. I've got you. I've got you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.22,1:35:40.79,Chs,,0,0,0,,在个人性情方面\N{\rEng}I'm not particularly adept at expressing myself
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.89,1:35:44.66,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不太擅于表达自己\N{\rEng}when it comes to matters of a more personal nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.50,1:35:49.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,但我会努力的\N{\rEng}But I shall try.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.11,1:35:54.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,这些年以来 我的行为方式\N{\rEng}Over the years, I have acted in ways
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.08,1:35:59.34,Chs,,0,0,0,,可能让你觉得太过严苛\N{\rEng}that you have judged to be harsh.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.42,1:36:06.85,Chs,,0,0,0,,我不想让你遭受更多痛苦了\N{\rEng}Well, I do not wish for you to undergo any further suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.86,1:36:14.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,事实上 我希望我们两个能和平相处\N{\rEng}In fact, I would like our lives to find a calm normality.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.80,1:36:26.97,Chs,,0,0,0,,为了祝贺你长假归来\N{\rEng}Lady Melbourne has arranged a small gathering
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.07,1:36:30.41,Chs,,0,0,0,,梅尔本夫人安排了一场小型聚会\N{\rEng}in honor of your recent return from holiday.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.54,1:36:34.11,Chs,,0,0,0,,过去这一年 外面流传着不少风言风语\N{\rEng}And given some of the vague reports that have been circulating this past year
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.25,1:36:36.88,Chs,,0,0,0,,我想我们双双出席就是最好的还击\N{\rEng}I think it would be wise for us to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.79,1:36:41.02,Chs,,0,0,0,,向世人证明 我们已经和好如初\N{\rEng}A show of unity, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.86,1:36:46.49,Chs,,0,0,0,,有哪些人出席？\N{\rEng}Who will be there?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.80,1:36:50.13,Chs,,0,0,0,,所有人\N{\rEng}Everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.27,1:37:02.64,Chs,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\rEng}As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.22,1:37:50.45,Chs,,0,0,0,,那样无拘无束 多好啊\N{\rEng}How wonderful to be that free.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.14,1:38:08.51,Chs,,0,0,0,,过来啊\N{\rEng}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.92,1:38:20.18,Chs,,0,0,0,,过来 小乔 过来\N{\rEng}Come here. Little G, come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.63,1:38:38.63,Chs,,0,0,0,,德文郡公爵和公爵夫人 伊丽莎白·福斯特夫人\N{\rEng}The Duke and Duchess of Devonshire and Lady Elizabeth Foster.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.82,1:38:53.15,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 夫人  - 见到你太好了\N{\rEng}- Your Grace.  - It's lovely to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.25,1:38:55.24,Chs,,0,0,0,,欢迎回来 夫人\N{\rEng}Welcome back, Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.66,1:38:59.99,Chs,,0,0,0,,请原谅\N{\rEng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.83,1:39:04.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 欢迎回来  - 欢迎回家 夫人\N{\rEng}- Welcome back.  - Welcome home, Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.20,1:39:07.10,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 欢迎回来  - 欢迎回来 乔\N{\rEng}- Welcome back.  - Welcome back, G.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.20,1:39:09.76,Chs,,0,0,0,,大家都很想念你\N{\rEng}Your presence has been sorely missed.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.74,1:39:51.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,对不起 离开一会儿\N{\rEng}Would you excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.01,1:39:57.48,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 格雷先生  - 夫人\N{\rEng}- Mr. Grey.  - Your Grace.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.89,1:40:03.19,Chs,,0,0,0,,相信您的旅程一定很愉快\N{\rEng}I trust your tour was enjoyable.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.76,1:40:06.28,Chs,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.39,1:40:10.26,Chs,,0,0,0,,我们在瑞士度夏 又去了尼斯避冬\N{\rEng}We spent the summer in Switzerland and the winter in Nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.36,1:40:12.46,Chs,,0,0,0,,在这里我代表大家\N{\rEng}Well, I speak on behalf of everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.57,1:40:16.47,Chs,,0,0,0,,为您能平安返回而感到由衷高兴\N{\rEng}when I say how glad I am that you have arrived home safely.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.84,1:40:23.04,Chs,,0,0,0,,你最近怎么样？\N{\rEng}And what news with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.35,1:40:27.01,Chs,,0,0,0,,我马上就要订婚了\N{\rEng}I'm to be engaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.95,1:40:31.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,和庞森比小姐\N{\rEng}To Lady Ponsonby.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.52,1:40:36.08,Chs,,0,0,0,,很快就会通知大家\N{\rEng}The announcement will follow shortly.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.72,1:40:39.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,恭喜你\N{\rEng}Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.80,1:40:46.53,Chs,,0,0,0,,我有个侄女 伊莱莎\N{\rEng}And I have a niece, Eliza,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.90,1:40:51.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,我非常疼爱她\N{\rEng}who is very much loved.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.21,1:41:02.70,Chs,,0,0,0,,哪天你来见见她吧\N{\rEng}One day you should come and meet her,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.95,1:41:05.61,Chs,,0,0,0,,如果你愿意\N{\rEng}in a little while.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.75,1:41:09.42,Chs,,0,0,0,,可以过一阵子就来\N{\rEng}If you would like.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.39,1:41:14.52,Chs,,0,0,0,,我非常愿意\N{\rEng}I would like that very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.25,1:41:38.75,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,500)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(980,635)\c&HD5E6E4&}乔治安娜重归上流社会 成为同时代最具盛名与权势的女性
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.00,1:41:46.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,500)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(980,750)\c&HD5E6E4&}查尔斯·格雷后来当选为首相
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.10,1:42:06.20,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,500)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(975,630)\c&HD5E6E4&}乔治安娜、贝丝和公爵共同生活在一起 直到乔治安娜离世
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.20,1:42:27.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,500)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(975,630)\c&HD5E6E4&}带着乔治安娜临终前的祝福 贝丝嫁入爵门 成为新的德文郡公爵夫人
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.88,1:42:40.81,Chs,,0,0,0,,看你们谁能抓到我？\N{\rEng}Who's going to catch me first?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.32,1:42:45.84,Chs,,0,0,0,,- 我！ - 快点 姑娘们\N{\rEng}- Me!  - Quick, girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.95,1:42:48.92,Chs,,0,0,0,,快来啊 否则我就跑掉喽！\N{\rEng}Quick, I'm going to get away!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.02,1:42:53.09,Chs,,0,0,0,,快啊 姑娘们 别停下\N{\rEng}Come on, girls, keep running.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.85,1:42:58.95,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,500)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(980,750)\c&HD5E6E4&\4a&H00&}乔治安娜常与伊莱莎秘密见面
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.10,1:43:08.60,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,500)\fs42\bord0\shad2\blur0\pos(980,635)\c&HD5E6E4&\4a&H00&}伊莱莎将自己的女儿取名为“乔治安娜”
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.00,1:43:06.80,Chs,,0,0,0,,我爱你 我也爱你\N{\rEng}And I love you, and I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.20,1:44:42.65,Chs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1500,1000)\fs80\fsp18\pos(960,530)\c&HD5E6E4&}公爵夫人

